# Yoni Authoring

## Every block requires

- block keyword + name
- `id:` — stable machine address (diagnostics target IDs, not line numbers)
- `desc:` — first-class metadata

## Typed references only

```
@Entity.Customer
@Intent.CreateInvoice
@Rule.Adult
```

Never use free strings like `"CreateInvoice"`.

## Intent section order (mandatory)

```
input: → validate: → process: → emit: → fail: → return:
```

Linter rejects reordered, missing, or duplicate sections.

## Rules

- One top-level block per file
- kebab-case filenames matching block name
- Machine-checkable rules: `customer.active == true`, not prose
- Actions = side effects only; business logic lives in rules/intents
- Entities are canonical schema — no raw objects

## ID prefixes

| Block | Prefix |
|-------|--------|
| entity | `ENT_` |
| intent | `INT_` |
| rule | `RULE_` |
| query | `QUERY_` |
| action | `ACT_` |
| event | `EVT_` |
| error | `ERR_` |
| state | `STS_` |
| constraint | `CNST_` |
| test | `TST_` |
| capability | `CAP_` |
| view | `VIEW_` |
| deployment | `DEP_` |
| migration | `MIG_` |
| domain | `DOM_` |
| project | `PROJ_` |
| workflow | `WF_` |

